When I receive an email for an issue where the assignee was changed from Joris de Goffau to me (Gillis J. de Nijs), it renders as:

*Assignee:* {color:#d04437}-Joris-{color} {color:#14892c}Gillis J.{color} de {color:#d04437}-Goffau-{color} {color:#14892c}Nijs{color}

In my opinion, usernames should be treated as a single entity and not be split up:

*Assignee:* {color:#d04437}-Joris de Goffau-{color} {color:#14892c}Gillis J. de Nijs{color}

That makes it easier to read.

h2.Summary

While requesting for projects, Jira is giving 200 OK with empty response: While making request for projects with expired cookie, Jira is giving 200 OK with empty json response. 

{quote}
If you use REST with a cookie that has expired, you will receive a 401 error response from JIRA. The response body will contain a message telling you that your cookie is invalid. At that point, you will need to re-authenticate to the session resource on the "auth" API.
{quote}

It should be giving 401 for unauthorized request as per the standards.

* https://developer.atlassian.com/jiradev/jira-apis/jira-rest-apis/jira-rest-api-tutorials/jira-rest-api-example-cookie-based-authentication


